	* scrollkeeper.spec.in: s/Copyright/License/

	* .cvsignore: Ignore some more rubbish.

2002-09-22  Malcolm Tredinnick <malcolm@commsecure.com.au>

	* po/POTFILES.in: Added a couple of files with translatable
	strings noticed by Kjartan Maraas <kmaraas@online.no>.

	* po/no.po: New Norwegian (bokmÃ¥l) translation thanks to Kjartan
	Maraas.

	* po/nb.po: Removed. It was a duplicate of no.po.

	* po/stamp-cat-id, po/cat-id-tbl.c: Removed. These should not be
	in CVS.

	* configure.in: Removed nb from ALL_LINGUAS.

	* cl/src/update.c: Applied patch from Owen Taylor
	<otaylor@redhat.com> to make scrollkeeper-update a bit quieter
	in non-verbose mode. Useful for packaging tools (bug #574338).

	* libs/extract.c, cl/src/get-cl.c: Applied patch from Alexander
	Larsson <alexl@redhat.com> to fix the recent symlink-following
	security problem.

	* libs/.cvsignore, cl/src/.cvsignore, scripts/.cvsignore,
	man/man?/.cvsignore, buildtools/.cvsignore, config/.cvsignore,
	cv/templates/.cvsignore, extract/.cvsignore,
	extract/dtds/.cvsignore, extract/src/.cvsignore,
	extract/stylesheets/.cvsignore,
	writing_scrollkeeper_omf_files/.cvsignore,
	writing_scrollkeeper_omf_files/C/.cvsignore, libuuid/.cvsignore,
	po/.cvsignore:
	Ignore a truckload of generated files. Some of these files are
	new, others have been updated.

2002-09-09  Malcolm Tredinnick <malcolm@commsecure.com.au>

	* libs/i18n.c: Fallback through a range of possible locales if
	the first choice is not found.

	* man/man8/scrollkeeper-update.8: Fix a typo.

	* Makefile.am, extract/dtds/Makefile.am, doc/omf.make:
	Apply patch from Marcus Meissner (SuSE) to move comments outside
	of command sections and fix problem with newer automakes (bug
	#573006).

	* cl/src/Makefile.am, cl/src/update.c: Respect the setting of
	sysconfdir when reading the configuration file.

	* libs/Makefile.am, libs/extract.c: Respect the setting of
	statedir when creating temporary files.

	* TODO: Removed a couple of items that have now been done.

